Reflect:
The results are striking. By moving from 'Pushes' (where every agent repeats what it knows) to 'Pointers' on a Shared Blackboard, we have effectively decoupling the coordination layer from the payload layer. The Token Gap is real; by only shipping pointers, our inter-agent bandwidth is almost entirely dedicated to novel signals rather than state replication. I suspect this also prevents 'semantic drift', as each agent reads directly from the source instead of reading another agent's summary of that source.

